Definition: superficially impressive, but lacking depth and attention to the true complexities of a subject
Example: too facile a solution for so complex a problem; it was a neat plan, but bound to fail; a slick advertising campaign
Synonyms: neat, slick, superficially, impressive, but, lacking, depth, and, attention, to, the, true, complexities, of, a, subject, too, solution, for, so, complex, problem, it, was, plan, bound, fail, advertising, campaign
Category: adj.all
